        -:  156:// Neither MSVC nor the Intel compiler define a macro for the POPCNT processor
        -:  157:// feature, so we're using either the SSE4.2 or the AVX macro as a proxy (Clang
        -:  158:// does define the macro). It's incorrect for two reasons:
        -:  159:// 1. It's a separate bit in CPUID, so a processor could implement SSE4.2 and
        -:  160://    not POPCNT, but that's unlikely to happen.
        -:  161:// 2. There are processors that support POPCNT but not AVX (Intel Nehalem
        -:  162://    architecture), but unlike the other compilers, MSVC has no option
        -:  163://    to generate code for those processors.
        -:  164:// So it's an acceptable compromise.
